by Kiu Ghesik » Sun Nov 08, 2020 1:35 pm

Uinted Communist of Africa wrote:They jokingly refer to their own nation as "A nation of angry horse boys" but they actually have a realistic religion that seems like it could have been one the mongolians used. Also their nation itself seems to pretty much be mongialia with a spin. And the ooc character was pretty funny.

There's a reason for the first bit. There's definitely a bit of Tengri aesthetic thrown in there. However, the ultimate view of the religion's theology is much closer to a mix of deism and Mesopotamian religion, in that it believes in a mechanical cosmos, a duality of man, and the earth as inferior to the gods, as compared to Tengrism where the earth is the meeting-place of a higher and lower deity, Tengri and Eje respectively. That is, if I understand Tengrism's philosophy correctly. My underlying assumptions might be entirely incorrect.

The second bit, eh... they're much more similar to the Caucasus nomads and the Scythians, but there's definitely some Mongol inspiration as well.
